      "content": "The statement that some people are \"meant to be stuck\" reflects a deep despair born from years of fighting against circumstances, but it is worth noting that this belief is often a symptom of the cycle itself rather than an unchangeable truth. While choosing not to play the game can be a valid moment of rest and boundary-setting, trying an experiment with a different, smaller version of engagement can sometimes reveal the loop was never involuntary until you committed to stopping. Often, the breaking point comes not from never trying again, but from shifting from a mindset of inevitable failure to one where the possibility of change, however small, is still on the table.",
